OL,3,CInexperienced climbers to be banned
OL,4,Cfrom climbing Everest following
OL,5,Ctraffic jams
OL,7,FThis is compared to approximately 953
OL,8,Fpeople in 2024, and 854 the year
OL,9,Fbefore that.
OL,11,FWhilst the database previously
OL,12,Finterviewed each climber to reach the
OL,13,Fsummit, this is now no longer possible
OL,14,Fdue to increasing numbers.
OL,16,FIn 2019, photographs went viral of a
OL,17,F"traffic jam" of climbers waiting on
OL,18,Fthe Hillary Step, a ridge above 8,000
OL,19,Fmeters in a "death zone", where oxygen
OL,20,Fis just a third of that at sea level.
